SMART SUBSCRIPTION & USAGE-BASED BILLING ENGINE

This C++ backend system simulates a SaaS billing platform. It manages subscription plans, tracks usage metrics, applies dynamic pricing rules, calculates discounts and taxes, and generates monthly invoices using core OOP principles.

--------------------------------------------------

OOP DESIGN STRUCTURE

Abstraction is implemented using abstract classes like BillingStrategy and PricingRule.

Inheritance is used where FreePlan, ProPlan, and EnterprisePlan extend SubscriptionPlan.

Polymorphism is used by overriding calculateBill() for different plan types.

Encapsulation is applied in classes like UsageMetrics and BillingDetails using private members.

Composition is used where Subscription contains AddOns and UsageMetrics.

Interfaces are implemented via DiscountPolicy and TaxCalculator using pure virtual functions.

Open-Closed Principle is followed by allowing new PricingRule classes without modifying existing code.

--------------------------------------------------

PROJECT STRUCTURE

smart_billing_engine/
- main.cpp
- models/
- billing/
- policies/
- invoice/
- interface/

--------------------------------------------------

CORE MODELS

User class stores id, name, and email with getters and display function.

SubscriptionPlan is an abstract base class with:
- calculateBill() as pure virtual
- getPlanName()
- getBasePrice()
- displayPlanDetails()

Derived classes:

FreePlan:
- Returns 0 if usage <= FREE_LIMIT
- Charges overage beyond limit

ProPlan:
- Base price + usage * rate per unit

EnterprisePlan:
- Flat negotiated rate regardless of usage

--------------------------------------------------

USAGE TRACKING & PRICING ENGINE

BillingStrategy is an abstract class with:
- calculate(usage, rate)
- strategyName()

Derived strategies:
- FlatRateStrategy
- PerUnitStrategy (usage * rate)
- TieredStrategy (multi-level pricing)

UsageMetrics structure stores:
- apiCalls
- storageGB
- activeUsers
- month
- year

UsageTracker:
- Records API calls, storage, users
- Stores data using nested map: userId → date → UsageMetrics
- Retrieves usage by user and date
- Resets monthly usage
- Displays usage

PricingRule abstract class:
- apply(baseAmount)
- ruleName()

Derived rules:
- ProratedRule (based on days used)
- VolumeDiscountRule (discount if amount exceeds threshold)

PricingEngine:
- Takes SubscriptionPlan, UsageMetrics, and PricingRules
- Computes total by applying plan calculation and rules sequentially

--------------------------------------------------

DISCOUNTS, TAXES & ADD-ONS

DiscountPolicy interface:
- applyDiscount(amount)
- discountName()

Implementations:
- NoDiscount
- PercentageDiscount
- SeasonalDiscount

TaxCalculator interface:
- calculateTax(amount)
- taxName()

Implementations:
- GSTCalculator (fixed percentage)
- VATCalculator (custom rate)

AddOn class:
- Stores name and monthly price
- Has display function

AddOnFactory:
- Creates predefined add-ons like Analytics, Backup, Priority Support

Helper function:
- applyAllAddOns() returns total cost of all add-ons

Billing flow:
baseAmount → applyDiscount → applyTax → addAddOns → finalBill

--------------------------------------------------

INVOICE SYSTEM

LineItem structure:
- description
- amount

Invoice class:
- Stores userId, month, year
- Stores list of line items
- Stores discount and tax info

Functions:
- addLineItem()
- setDiscount()
- setTax()
- getSubtotal()
- getTotal()
- printInvoice()
- saveToFile()

InvoiceGenerator:
- Generates invoice using:
  - SubscriptionPlan
  - UsageTracker
  - DiscountPolicy
  - TaxCalculator
  - AddOns

Generation logic:
1. Get usage metrics
2. Calculate base bill using plan
3. Add base line item
4. Add add-ons as line items
5. Apply discount
6. Apply tax
7. Return final invoice

--------------------------------------------------

CLI INTERFACE

Menu-driven system with options:
- Manage Users
- Manage Subscriptions
- Track Usage
- Configure Billing
- Generate Invoice
- Display Users & Plans

Interface class:
- Runs loop for menu
- Handles user actions
- Maintains mapping of user to subscription plan

--------------------------------------------------

INVOICE CALCULATION LOGIC

Subtotal = sum of all line items

Total = subtotal - discount + tax

--------------------------------------------------

TEST SCENARIOS

- Free plan with zero usage → bill = 0
- Pro plan exceeding usage → overage applied
- Enterprise plan → flat rate billing
- Seasonal discount applied correctly
- Multiple add-ons added correctly
- Prorated billing works for partial usage

--------------------------------------------------

COMPILATION

Use g++ with all source files and C++17 standard.

--------------------------------------------------

DEVELOPMENT APPROACH

- Build modules independently
- Follow OOP principles strictly
- Integrate all components at the end
- Test with multiple users and plans